cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on using geometric data analysis to analyze narrative, specifically focusing on the analysis of emotion. This falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of unsupervised learning and mapping techniques also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the analysis of social context and the use of data from Twitter streams suggests a connection to social computing (cs.SI) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
